+
+Updated the fallback preview payload in `src/policy/preview.py` so the
+`preview_unavailable` response now preserves `approval_state` and
+`requires_human_review` alongside the existing status/actor fields.
+
+### T-214-02
+
+No separate code change. This thread is a duplicate of `T-214-01`, and the
+same fallback payload fix covers the reopened regression.
+
+### T-214-03
+
+Not applying this suggestion. The review export marks it outdated, and reviving
+legacy preview branching here would reintroduce retired behavior on the current
+branch.
+
+### T-214-04
+
+Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` covering
+`preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` routed through
+`build_policy_preview(...)`. The assertion now locks the normalized fallback
+payload to `approval_state="human_review_required"` with
+`requires_human_review=True`.
+
+### T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now matches the fixed
+payload, including `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+`requires_human_review=true`.
