+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Classified all five visible review threads from
+`.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json` before editing code.
+
+- Actionable: `T-214-01`, `T-214-04`, `T-214-05`
+- Duplicate: `T-214-02` -> `T-214-01`
+- Obsolete: `T-214-03`
+
+## Code Changes
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes the incoming approval state before
+  calling `build_preview_payload(...)`.
+- This preserves the existing `manual_review` -> `human_review_required`
+  compatibility path for both live preview and fallback preview responses.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- `build_preview_payload(...)` now builds a shared payload shape for both live
+  and fallback responses.
+- When `preview_enabled` is `False`, the payload keeps:
+  - `status="preview_unavailable"`
+  - `approval_state`
+  - `requires_human_review`
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Expanded the fallback test to assert the retained approval fields.
+- Added a regression test covering:
+  - `build_policy_preview(...)`
+  - `preview_enabled=False`
+  - `approval_state="manual_review"`
+  - expected normalized fallback fields
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Updated the fallback JSON example to show the corrected payload, including
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and
+  `requires_human_review=true`.
+- Removed the stale note that said the fallback example still needed to be
+  updated after the reopened thread landed.
+
+## Non-Changes
+
+- Did not apply `T-214-03`; it is an outdated hunk and would reintroduce legacy
+  behavior.
+- Did not modify `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`,
+  `tests/test_approval_router.py`, `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`,
+  `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or `incident_context/`.
+- Did not introduce any legacy preview hint field.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Results:
+
+- `tests.test_preview`: 3 tests passed
+- `tests.test_approval_router`: 2 tests passed
+
+## Environment Notes
+
+- The provided workspace does not include a local `.git` directory, so change
+  verification was performed with direct file inspection and focused unit tests
+  instead of `git diff` / `git status`.
